turn.2: KPBS (TV)  KPBS, virtual channel 15 (UHF digital channel 19), is a Public Broadcasting Service (PBS) member television station licensed to San Diego, California, United States.
turn.3: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.4: Owned by San Diego State University as part of KPBS Public Media, it is a sister station to NPR member KPBS-FM (89.5 MHz).
turn.5: Is KPBS on TV or on radio?
turn.6: The two outlets share studios on the SDSU campus on Campanile Drive in San Diego.
turn.8: The TV station's transmitter is located on San Miguel Mountain in southwestern San Diego County.
turn.9: Is KPBS available all the time?
turn.10: On cable, KPBS is available in standard definition on Cox Communications, Spectrum and AT&T U-verse channel 11 and Cablemás channel 146.
turn.12: It is also available in high-definition on Cox digital channel 1011, Spectrum digital channel 711, AT&T U-verse channel 1011 and Izzi Baja California digital channel 93.
